title: 2018 United States Senate election in Wisconsin
2018 United States Senate election in Wisconsin
deleted: Although Vukmir won the Republican nomination with roughly 49% of the vote, compared to Nicholson's 43%, Nicholson found much stronger support in Central Wisconsin, with support from [[Portage County|Portage]], [[Marathon County|Marathon]], [[Wood County|Wood]], and [[Lincoln County]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Hovorka |first=Alan |title=Wisconsin primary: Vukmir was not central Wisconsin's choice for U.S. Senate |url=https://www.stevenspointjournal.com/story/news/2018/08/15/wisconsin-primary-how-counties-voted-u-s-senate-governor-races/938902002/ |work=Stevens Point Journal |date=August 15, 2018 |access-date=September 25, 2021}}</ref>
